# Anchored to repo root with a leading slash. Without it, gitignore
# patterns match any directory of that name at any depth — so an
# unanchored `build/` would silently shadow src/workflows/build/, an
# unanchored `dist/` would shadow any future src/.../dist/ fixture, etc.
# Same trap as the prior `build/` shadowing bug; keep all three anchored.
/node_modules/
/dist/
/build/
.DS_Store
*.log
.env
.env.local
coverage/
.vitest-cache/
.turbo/
.circuit-next/
.claude/projects/
.claude/worktrees/
# Runtime lock from the Claude Code harness (sessionId/pid/acquiredAt). Not
# a deliverable; per-machine ephemeral state.
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# Tool-run state for the Circuit harness used by this project. Ephemeral
# per-machine state; nothing here is a deliverable.
.circuit/
